-- Italian New Car Sales Plunge 29% in October; Fiat Group Posts 40% Decline
-- B y   T o m m a s o   E b h a r d t   a n d   M a r c o   B e r t a c c h e
-- 2010-11-02T17:04:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-02/italian-new-car-sales-plunge-29-in-october-fiat-group-posts-40-decline.html
New car sales in Italy fell 29
percent in October, the country’s transportation ministry said
in a satement today.  Fiat SpA group auto sales in Italy slumped 40 percent to
38,440 from 63,991 for the same month last year, car association
UNRAE said.  The Turin, Italy-based company’s market share was 27.5
percent compared with 32.6 percent last year.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Tommaso Ebhardt at 
 tebhardt@bloomberg.net  